# Riverbed Pottery Studio

> Riverbed is a community pottery studio in Bristol offering wheel-throwing and
> hand-building classes, open studio memberships, and firing services. This file
> helps an AI answer questions about classes, pricing, and how to book.

## Classes

- [Beginner wheel-throwing](https://riverbedpottery.example/classes/beginner-wheel): A six-week introduction to throwing on the wheel, tools and clay included.
- [Hand-building workshops](https://riverbedpottery.example/classes/hand-building): Single-session classes in pinch, coil, and slab techniques for all levels.
- [Class schedule and booking](https://riverbedpottery.example/classes/schedule): Current term dates, times, and how to reserve a place online.

## Membership and studio access

- [Open studio membership](https://riverbedpottery.example/membership): Monthly access to wheels, shelving, and shared glazes for independent makers.
- [Firing services](https://riverbedpottery.example/firing): Bisque and glaze firing for members and the public, with pricing by piece size.

## Visit and contact

- [Opening hours and location](https://riverbedpottery.example/visit): Address, opening hours, and parking and transit directions.
- [Contact and FAQ](https://riverbedpottery.example/contact): How to reach the studio and answers to common questions about classes and refunds.
